results.description: A light bulb lit magically without electricity. Should objects be allowed to act on their own ? Or only us humans should wire bulbs, toggle switches and use them as we please ? Do we feel threatened by an object that defies us ? A bulb that lights during our absence because it does not want to live in the dark or for its own amusement ? A free spirit that does not need our electricity and the wire that keeps it our prisoner ? Are we talking consciousness here or are we talking master and servant ? If the object acted on its own will, would YOU allow it to ? Could YOU be happy that it does ?
